<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lane</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        José, Costa Rica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-05"><hi rend="italic">April
                                        5, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Consulate Bluefields, 30th, asks two war vessels; merchants ordered pay
                            Government duty immediately; already paid insurgent, otherwise suffer
                            consequences; martial law enforced; Government refused consul use wire;
                            am unable communicate minister.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lane.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>